<!--
        <question id="arch-overall" when="init">
            Describe the overall architecture. 
            <hint>
            What will be API for 
            <a href="http://openide.netbeans.org/tutorial/api-design.html#design.apiandspi">
                clients and what support API</a>? 
            What parts will be pluggable?
            How will plug-ins be registered? Please use <code>&lt;api type="export"/&gt;</code>
            to describe your general APIs and specify their
            <a href="http://openide.netbeans.org/tutorial/api-design.html#category-private">
            stability categories</a>.
            If possible please provide simple diagrams.
            </hint>
        </question>
-->
 <answer id="arch-overall">
  <p>
    The module provides no stable API.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Local History is listening for events from the filesystem, 
    stores files which where created, modified or deleted in the IDE and 
    provides an UI to overview the stored data, revert old changes and to setup 
    what files and for how long are to be hold in the local history.        
  </p>      
  
      <api group="java.io.File" name="localstorage" type="export" category="private">
          <p>
                A folder in $userdir/cache. Contains the Local History storage. 
          </p>        
      </api>  
      
      <api group="java.io.File" name="version" type="export" category="private">
      <p>
          One instance for the whole storage. Contains the storage version.
      </p>
      </api>

      <api group="java.io.File" name="versioned-file" type="export" category="private">
      <p>
          For every file or folder changed in the IDE there is a new folder with a generated name 
          created in the main storage folder. It contains metadata files and all stored previous versions 
          for the versioned file.
      </p>
      </api>

        The following files are created in the storage in case a file was changed:
        <ul>
          <li>      
            <api group="java.io.File" name="stored-version" type="export" category="private">
              <p>
                  One instance for every file change. Is a files version before it was changed. Zipped.
                  XXX
              </p>
              </api>        
          </li>   
          <li>
              <api group="java.io.File" name="data" type="export" category="private">
              <p>
                  One instance for each file changed in the IDE. Contains metadata describing its state and origin.
                  XXX
              </p>
              </api>
          </li>           
          <li>
              <api group="java.io.File" name="labels" type="export" category="private">
              <p>
                  One instance for each file changed in the IDE. Contains labels given to particular versions.
                  XXX
              </p>
              </api>
          </li>                   
        </ul>  
        
        The following files are created in the storage in case a folder was changed 
        <ul>  
          <li>
              <api group="java.io.File" name="history" type="export" category="private">
              <p>
                  One instance for each folder changed in the IDE. Contains information about structural changes. (file create, file delete, ...)
                  XXX
              </p>
              </api>
          </li>                 
        </ul>  

  <p>
    Open Issues:        
  </p>    
     <ul>            
         <li>the only event related to a file change comes after a file was already saved. 
         Not like in beforeDelete and deleteSuccess or beforeCreate and createSuccess</li>
     </ul>    
 </answer>



