 <answer id="exec-threading">
  <ul>
      <li>
            The module is listening on events from the filesystem and processes them synchronously by creating 
            relevant entries in the local history storage. 
      </li>     
      <li>
            Several actions retrieve data from the local history storage or modify files through calls on the 
            <code>org.openide.filesystems.FileObject</code> layer. Such data processing runs always asynchronously 
